&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant Anaesthetist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here at George Eliot our vision to &lt;em&gt;‘&lt;strong&gt;excel at patient care’&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; takes centre stage. An ever evolving clinically-led acute service provider we are on a journey to continually provide high quality, safe and responsive services delivered by inspiring, friendly and compassionate staff who share our corporate values which underpin everything we do. Our values are not just words on a piece of paper, they bond us together, reflect our ambition and shape who we are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;E&lt;/strong&gt;ffective Open Communication&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;e&lt;strong&gt;x&lt;/strong&gt;cellence and safety in everything we do&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C&lt;/strong&gt;hallenge but support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;E&lt;/strong&gt;xpect respect and dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L&lt;/strong&gt;ocal health that inspires confidence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint a Consultant Anaesthetist with interest in General Anaesthesia and Chronic Pain to our large, cohesive and forward-looking department. Candidates with particular sub-specialty interests are most welcome to apply. Please refer to the job packs for further details including the job plans and requirements for the posts. Please note the similarity of job plans which are different within our 2 week rota. Candidates are encouraged to apply and if successful can pick their preferred job plan at interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information or an informal discussion, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Meera Bryant, Clinical Director&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;or&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Liz Mathers General Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All members of the department can be contacted via our switchboard on 02476 351351&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must hold full GMC registration and should possess the ability to work in a multidisciplinary team, have good interpersonal skills, and have a caring attitude towards patients and evidence of good clinical practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please note, GEH are not currently holding pre-interview visits to the hospital on account of COVID-19 and current social distancing advice. However, we will be able to organise virtual pre-interview discussions with the department and members of the interview panel. For more information, please contact medicalstaffingteam@geh.nhs.uk&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Benefits&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our benefits include but are not limited to: On-site nursery, 27 days minimum annual leave plus 8 bank holidays, cycle to work scheme, flexible working, on-site discounted gym, extensive in-house course learning directory, buying and selling of annual leave, subsidised restaurant, tranquillity garden, generous and subsidised on-site parking, home electronics and white goods benefit scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: Friday 13th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: TBC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post may close early due to high numbers of applications &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;so you are advised to apply promptly.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All correspondence for this vacancy will be sent by email; please check your account regularly including your Junk and SPAM areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;A great and friendly place to work, so bring your passion, commitment and expertise &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;and enjoy the opportunities to make a difference every day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
